<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   9 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> COLOMBIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Bombs Explode in Medellin, Cause Damage; No Fatalities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0302134194 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1143 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0302134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 3 February (DPA) -- Two 
medium-intensity bombs exploded today in the Colombian city of 
Medellin. No fatalities were reported, but severe damage was 
caused, police have stated. 
  The first bomb exploded in front of a bank office in the 
center of the city. After the explosion, a fire broke out but 
was rapidly contained. 
  A second bomb exploded minutes later at the gate of the 
English Language Academy, which sustained severe damage. 
  According to police, these are new extremist actions 
perpetrated by movements that oppose the presence of U.S. 
soldiers in several parts of Colombia, where they have built 
bases for the Colombian Government to combat drug trafficking. 
  Two weeks ago terrorists detonated bombs against a Mormon 
church that was operated by U.S. citizens in the western part of 
Medellin. They also attacked other U.S. interests in this city, 
which is located in the northwestern part of Colombia. 
  (Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish at 
1200 GMT on 3 February, during its "Caracol's 0600-0900" 
newscast, adds: "Authorities have blamed guerrillas for the 
explosion of two bombs in the city of Medellin.") 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

