<H3> <TI>   Papers Cite Reports on Bid To Kill 'Arafat in Amman </TI></H3>
<H4>   Palestinians Said Arrested </H4>
<F P=102> JN0602205694 Baghdad AL-QADISIYAH in Arabic 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0602205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-QADISIYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- AL-QADISIYAH monitoring -- Jordanian 
authorities have disclosed an attempt to assassinate Mr. Yasir 
'Arafat during his latest visit to Amman. 
  They arrested a number of Palestinians, who were armed with 
RPG's with the intention of hitting 'Arafat's plane upon landing 
at the airport. The suspects admitted that they were planning 
to assassinate the Palestinian leader for signing the 
Gaza-Jericho accord with the Zionist enemy. 
  [Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic on 3 February publishes a 
front 
page MENA report citing Palestinian sources in Amman as saying 
that Jordan's intelligence services aborted an attempt to kill 
'Arafat during his latest visit to Amman by downing his plane as 
it landed at the airport]. 

</TEXT>

