<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Adviser: Hawks Part of `National Authority' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802155094 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 5 Feb 94 pp 1, 19 </F>
<F P=103> TA0802155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Da'ud Kuttab] </F>
  [Excerpt] Jerusalem -- Jibril al-Rajub, adviser to 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, has protested the killing 
of Salim Muwafi, the Fatah Hawks leader in Gaza, by the Israeli 
forces. He considered this act as an attempt to kill the peace 
process. 
  In an exclusive interview with AL-QUDS, al-Rajub said that 
the Palestinian leadership regards the Fatah Hawks as part of 
the forces that have to protect the national authority. 
Consequently, we have to provide security for them. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

