<H3> <TI>   DFLP, PFLP, Hizballah Officials Speak in al-Yarmuk Camp </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0502105194 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0515 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0502105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Nayif Hawatimah, secretary general of the 
Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP], has 
condemned the Gaza-Jericho agreement and the Taba-Davos 
negotiations. [passage omitted] 
  Addressing a crowded ceremony in al-Yarmuk camp in Damascus 
yesterday on the DFLP's 25th anniversary, Hawatimah said that 
the Oslo-Davos agreement [as heard] is a partial and separate 
agreement that gives nothing in return. He noted that this 
agreement was concluded behind the backs of the Palestinian 
people and their intifadah and that it is bound to fail. 
  'Abu-'Ali Mustafa, deputy secretary general of the Popular 
Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP], also delivered a 
speech on behalf of the joint PFLP-DFLP command and the alliance 
of Palestinian forces. Sayf Bin-'Ali also delivered a speech on 
behalf of the Arab liberation parties and movements, and 'Ammar 
al-Musawi, deputy head of Hizballah's Political Bureau, 
delivered a speech on behalf of the Lebanese national and 
Islamic resistance. [passage omitted] 
  The rally was attended by a number of secretary generals, 
members of political bureaus and central committees of 
Palestinian factions, a number of representatives of the 
Lebanese national and Islamic movement and Arab liberation 
movements, some members of the diplomatic corps accredited to 
Damascus, and a crowd of citizens. 

</TEXT>

