<H3> <TI>   Witness in Fundamentalists' Trial Murdered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0502071094 Cairo MENA in English 2350 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0502071094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Feb 4 (MENA)--Ahmad Yahya, owner of a car 
agency in Shibin al-Qanatir, lower Egypt, was killed tonight 
along with two others when unidentified persons opened fire at 
his workplace. Another person was wounded in the incident. 
  Senior Interior Ministry officials rushed to the scene and 
started investigations. 
  [Paris AFP in English at 0147 on 5 February, in a related 
Cairo-datelined item, adds the following: 
  ["Gunmen late Friday shot dead four people here, including a 
prosecution witness in a trial of Moslem fundamentalists, police 
reported. 
  ["They said unidentified assailants opened fire on Sayyid 
Ahmad Yahya, an automobile dealer, in his showroom. 
  ["Three other people at the scene -- a security guard, an 
employee and a client -- were killed and a policeman was hurt, 
police said. 
  ["Yahya was a government witness in the trial of Moslem 
militants accused of having tried to assassinate Egyptian Prime 
Minister 'Atif Sidqi. 
  ["Those charged in the attack on Sidqi are alleged to have 
bought a car from Yahya that was then booby-trapped as part of 
the November 25 attempt on the prime minister's life. 
  ["A second hearing in the trial of nine fundamentalists 
accused of plotting to kill Sidqi was scheduled to open here on 
Saturday. They are members of the Tala'i' al-Fath (The Leaders 
of the Conquest), considered by authorities to be the military 
wing of Al-Jihad fundamentalist movement, which claimed 
responsibility for the operation against the prime minister."] 

</TEXT>

