<H3> <TI>   Islamic Group Reiterates Threat Against Foreigners </TI></H3>
<H4>   Vanguards Condemn Islamic Group Threats </H4>
<F P=102> JN0702190894 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 7 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0702190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dispatch by Ahmad Idris in Islamabad] </F>
  [Text] Severe differences have surfaced among Egyptian 
Islamic groups regarding the warnings issued to foreigners that 
they should leave the country. In a statement to our radio by 
telephone, the official in charge of the Information Bureau of 
the Conquest Vanguards Organization [tanzim tala'i al-fatah] 
condemned, on behalf of the organization, the warning issued 
three days ago by the al-Jama'ah al-Islamiyah to foreigners and 
its threats to strike at foreign investors and their projects in 
Egypt. He said: 
  [Begin recording] The Islamic masses and the whole nation 
know that Islam -- as all scholars have always been unanimous -- 
has forbidden any act that harms the Muslims. Thus, striking at 
the Egyptian economy and at legal investments will harm the 
Muslim masses there. [end recording] 
  The statement notes that this will isolate the Islamists and 
provide excuses to uproot them. The statement calls on the 
Egyptian leadership to apply the Islamic law and wipe out 
hotbeds of corruption to end armed confrontation and improve the 
situation. 

</TEXT>

