<H3> <TI>   IG Targets Bank System, Kills Asyut Policeman </TI></H3>
<H4>   Bomb Near Central Bank in Cairo; 2 Defused </H4>
<F P=102> NC0702222494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2147 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0702222494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Feb (MENA)--An explosive device went off 
this evening near the Egyptian Central Bank, opposite the 
al-Fath Mosque, on Ramsis Street in Cairo. According to 
preliminary reports, the explosion caused no casualties. 
However, there was some damage to the bank's outside windows. 
  Meanwhile, Interior Ministry explosives experts have defused 
two bombs--one placed near the Muhammad Faris branch of the Bank 
of Egypt, and the second near the National Bank on Sharif 
Street, in central Cairo. 
  Security commanders and criminal laboratory experts went to 
the site of the explosion to investigate. 

</TEXT>

