<H3> <TI>   BJP Worker Killed in Bomb Blast in Kanpur; Violence Erupts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0902161294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0902161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Uttar Pradesh, curfew has been imposed in 
(Babupurva) area of Kanpur following the death of a BJP 
[Bharatiya Janata Party] worker in a bomb attack. The situation 
in the area is stated to be tense, but under control. A senior 
police official told our Kanpur correspodent that as the news of 
the BJP worker's death spread an unruly mob set on fire the car 
of the minister of state for revenue, Mr. Babu Ram Yadav. 
However, the minister escaped unhurt. Additional companies of 
paramilitary forces are being rushed to Kanpur City. 
  [Hong Kong AFP in English at 1443 GMT on 9 February, in a 
similar report, adds: "At least one person was killed, three 
others injured and some 10 homes burned in the northern city of 
Kanpur Wednesday after a Hindu politician was slain in a bomb 
blast," the PRESS TRUST OF INDIA (PTI) said. 
  "Frenzied Hindus torched six houses and two shops, burned 
several cars and attacked government property following the 
death of Kala Bachha of the Hindu-revivalist Bharatiya Janata 
Party (BJP, Indian People's Party). 
  "Bachha died instantly in the explosion and a Hindu friend 
accompanying him was seriously injured, the news agency said. 
  "Further details of the bomb attack or the subsequent arson 
and violence were not available. 
  "An official said a curfew had been imposed in certain 
sections of the city as a precautionary measure and educational 
institutions ordered to remain shut on Thursday. Security has 
also been stepped up."] 

</TEXT>

