  The charges went off at 1300 on Monday, 7 February, 1994, 
destroying the factory and setting huge fires that spread to 
neighboring factories and installations. 
  The military spokesman added that, since the operation, 
rescue and fire fighting teams, the police, and the mobile 
environment protection unit for treating dangerous materials 
have been making great attempts to place the situation under 
control, while clouds of black smoke covered the whole Gulf of 
Haifa. 

