<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, Feb 5 (AA) -- On Saturday, Syrian Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar' expressed his country's concern over the 
lack of a `water sharing agreement' between Turkey, adding it 
will be a source for tension as long as such an agreement is not 
signed. [passage omitted] 
  On the terrorism issue, al-Shar' said that Damascus fully 
supports Turkey's territorial integrity, reiterating that Syria 
does not support the terrorist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] 
organization. 
