denounces any kind of terrorism. 
  However al-Shar' did not qualify the terrorist PKK 
organization as `terrorist.' Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin, 
who held the opening speech of the meeting, said that the 
tripartite consultation meeting was held to evaluate the latest 
situation in the region where the three countries are situated 
specially the developments in Iraq, adding it is not directed 
against any other country. 
  He said the protection of Iraq's territorial unity is as 
vital for the three countries concerned as for the whole world, 
adding the support or incentives towards separatist movements is 
unacceptable, a point also stressed by Syria and Iran. [passage 
omitted] 

