<H3> <TI>   Youth Group Threatens Terrorism If Aliyev Does Not Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702205394 Yerevan SNARK in English 1244 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0702205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, Feb 7, (SNARK) -- Confidential sources in Baku 
told SNARK that the youth patriotic organization entering the 
Azerbaijani People's Front has appealed Geydar Aliyev to resign 
as a president. Otherwise, the organization threatens to effect 
terrorist and sabotage acts on Azerbaijan territory. 
  In this connection, the official circles in Azerbaijan do 
not 
rule out that the recent explosion in the Baku-Kislovodsk 
passenger train was undertaken by fighters of this organization. 

