<H3> <TI>   Reported Lautaro Group Members Hold Up Santiago Banks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0902202994 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1700 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0902202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Individuals who identified themselves as Lautaro 
Group members held up a bank in the Providencia neighborhood. 
The thieves, who fired their weapons at Carabineros officers as 
they fled, seized 15 million pesos. 
  Eight Lautaro Group members tried to simultaneously hold up 
two banks on the corner of Suecia and 11 September Streets. 
However, they only managed to hold up the Santander Bank. The 
presence of Carabineros on the corner prompted the group 
planning to hold up the Citibank branch a few meters away to 
flee. 
  As they fled, the delinquents fired their weapons at a group 
of policemen travelling in a patrol van. Once again a woman was 
seen firing a machine gun. [passage omitted] 

