<H3> <TI>   Army Seizes Arms, Ammunition Intended for ELN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0602231394 Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 4 Feb 
94 p 8a </F>

<F P=103> PA0602231394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cucuta -- On Wednesday, the Army frustrated a 
terrorist plan prepared by the Guerrilla Coordinating Board 
(CGR) when the 5th Mechanized Group, based in Cucuta, seized a 
large amount of arms and ammunition intended for the ELN [Army 
of National Liberation]. 
  According to the version given by military detachment 
commander Colonel Henry Dominguez, the seizure dismantled a 
major part of the CGR's logistical structure tasked with 
supplying arms and quartermaster supplies to the various groups 
who operate in the Departments of Santander and Norte de 
Santander, the southern part of Cesar Department, and Bolivar 
Department. 
  The operation began at 0500 [1000 GMT] on 2 February and 
ended 12 hours later. Alfredo Angarita Torres, "Hermes," 
logistic wing leader of the northeastern war front; Jesus Emilio 
Ovalle Rodriguez, "Chucho;" and sisters Angelina and Barbara 
Perez Duran were captured in house No. 3-77 on 21st Avenue, in 
the Tasajero neighborhood. 

</TEXT>

