  [Text] A bomb of moderate intensity exploded in front of 
the Social Security's San Pedro Claver Clinic in Santa Fe de 
Bogota early this morning. The blast occurred a few meters from 
the district's administrative center. 
  The terrorist action caused no casualties but did cause 
serious damage to businesses and houses near the area. 
Authorities blame the guerrillas' urban commando units. 
  The Santa Fe de Bogota Metropolitan Police have arrested no 
one for this incident yet. 

