<H3> <TI>   Serial Bombings in Lima 7-8 Feb </TI></H3>
<H4>   Details on Banco de Credito Bombing </H4>
<F P=102> PA0802050294 Lima Panamericana Television Network in Spanish 
0300 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0802050294 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Panamericana Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Tonight terrorists hurled a package with explosives 
at the Banco de Credito branch located in Caqueta Avenue. The 
explosion caused minor injuries to three passersby and property 
damage to the bank. Other explosions were also reported tonight 
in Lima. 
  This is the fourth time subversive units have attacked the 
Banco de Credito located one block from Parque del Trabajo, 
between the districts of Rimac and San Martin de Porras. 
  The incident took place at approximately 2000 when a package 
with explosives was thrown by two terrorists traveling in a 
white Volkswagen. The blast damaged the bank's neon sign and 
also ruptured the potable water pipes. The police also reported 
similar attacks to local banks located in Peru and Mexico 
Avenues in La Victora. Only minor property damages and no 
casualties have been reported. 

</TEXT>

